00:03:15.760 --> 00:03:18.430
Inaccessible navigation gets fixed.

00:03:18.430 --> 00:03:20.510
Alt text gets added to images.

00:03:20.510 --> 00:03:21.860
Heading order is addressed.

00:03:21.860 --> 00:03:24.190
Captions added to videos.

00:03:24.190 --> 00:03:26.370
Color contrast improved.

00:03:26.370 --> 00:03:29.580
Then there are things that have
a broader range of options,

00:03:29.580 --> 00:03:32.970
things that can be seen as annoying,
that you're adding to the page.

00:03:32.970 --> 00:03:34.490
Optional things.

00:03:34.490 --> 00:03:37.620
So the first thing to consider
when adding something to a site,

00:03:37.620 --> 00:03:41.620
and I argue this question is
worth asking for a large amount

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:45.810
of things that can get added
to a site, Is this necessary?

00:03:45.810 --> 00:03:48.155
Can this be done in a
way that doesn't need

00:03:48.156 --> 00:03:50.961
an entirely separate
control or configuration?

00:03:50.962 --> 00:03:54.560
It's making sure there's a reason
for what you're doing.

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:58.530
In this case, our question is,
are the animations necessary?

00:03:58.530 --> 00:04:01.400
Can we use images to
achieve the same thing?

00:04:01.400 --> 00:04:06.340
Can someone get the same feeling from
some other method besides motion?

00:04:06.340 --> 00:04:10.030
In my case,
I had created my new agency website;

00:04:10.030 --> 00:04:13.510
and while I could have kept it
to pretty much almost all text,

00:04:13.510 --> 00:04:17.190
I knew I wanted to add
something to break it up.

00:04:17.190 --> 00:04:20.210
The options are sort of
limitless in this case, right?

00:04:20.210 --> 00:04:24.690
Use a lot of color, and image,
and icon, background image

00:04:24.690 --> 00:04:27.760
with a gradient,
something to give the eyes a break,

00:04:27.760 --> 00:04:30.780
reinforce the text,
and give a little bit of feeling.

00:04:30.780 --> 00:04:34.180
For Kinetic Iris,
we're a development studio.

00:04:34.180 --> 00:04:37.570
A lot of what we do does
not have the type of visuals

00:04:37.570 --> 00:04:40.730
that you would put on a page
that's enticing to the audience.

00:04:40.730 --> 00:04:42.980
It's just a bunch of code, right?

00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:44.780
Maybe some site examples.

00:04:44.780 --> 00:04:48.960
I didn't want to crawl through
hundreds of stock photos.

00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:51.360
I didn't want to go completely
in the opposite direction

00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:53.710
of simple icons or SVGs.

00:04:53.710 --> 00:04:55.050
I wanted it dynamic.

00:04:55.050 --> 00:04:57.970
The company name has
the word Kinetic in it.

00:04:57.970 --> 00:04:59.280
I wanted motion.

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:01.920
And it gives a little bit
more of that interactive field

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:04.360
to reinforce the custom
development side of things.

00:05:06.670 --> 00:05:09.860
In regards to the bigger
question of generally,

00:05:11.480 --> 00:05:13.650
is this something you just
want to throw on the site

00:05:13.650 --> 00:05:14.830
because you think it looks neat?

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:18.360
Is it something that
actually enhances the site?

00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:21.350
Is there a different way you
can convey this information

00:05:21.350 --> 00:05:26.220
or brand-feel without adding
