00:46:03.890 --> 00:46:05.530
why am I adding this?

00:46:05.530 --> 00:46:08.470
Is it going to cause any problems?

00:46:08.470 --> 00:46:11.420
Basically everything I
ran through in my journey

00:46:11.420 --> 00:46:15.140
of adding an accessibility,
single toggle is kind

00:46:15.140 --> 00:46:16.920
of how you approach
everything else.

00:46:16.920 --> 00:46:21.650
It's all about a process and
finding a couple of good resources.

00:46:21.650 --> 00:46:23.760
There's the WordPress
Accessibility Meetup.

00:46:23.760 --> 00:46:26.150
There's all kinds of blogs.

00:46:27.270 --> 00:46:31.070
Anything that you can find to
give you some starting points.

00:46:31.070 --> 00:46:33.520
And then once you learn one
thing, add on another.

00:46:34.850 --> 00:46:37.290
It's really just about starting.

00:46:37.290 --> 00:46:40.990
And once you start thinking about
things in terms of accessibility,

00:46:40.990 --> 00:46:43.960
that's kind of how you tend to
look at everything when it comes

00:46:43.960 --> 00:46:47.950
to websites, and you're always
looking through things in that lens.

00:46:47.950 --> 00:46:51.270
And it's really just about asking
questions, and being curious,

00:46:51.270 --> 00:46:54.700
and doing some research to try
to find the best way to do it.

00:46:54.700 --> 00:46:58.250
I would say look into
accessibility statements.

00:46:58.250 --> 00:47:02.920
I think a lot of times, if we give
people a great place to find us

00:47:02.920 --> 00:47:05.730
and report issues that they
have, and make it easy to find,

00:47:05.730 --> 00:47:09.410
stick it in the footer, and give
a very clear way to contact you,

00:47:09.410 --> 00:47:11.670
that's a good way to know what
problems people are having,

00:47:11.670 --> 00:47:12.920
and that's a good place to start.

00:47:14.510 --> 00:47:18.980
So I would just find ways
to start with things.

00:47:18.980 --> 00:47:20.460
Do the easy stuff.

00:47:20.460 --> 00:47:23.120
Like I had sort of rattled off
in the beginning, you have,

00:47:23.120 --> 00:47:26.910
like, heading order
and image alt text.

00:47:26.910 --> 00:47:31.840
An accessible navigation is really
hard to do as a beginner thing.

00:47:31.840 --> 00:47:34.950
So pick something and sort
of just dive right into it,

00:47:34.950 --> 00:47:36.390
and see where it takes you.

00:47:36.390 --> 00:47:38.160
Just kind of be in it
for the journey, I think.

